1.00	Bolivian_legislative_election,_1951	Bolivian legislative election, 1951	In the election, held on 6 May, Víctor Paz Estenssoro, the candidate of the opposition MNR, obtained the largest number of votes (54,129 out of 126,125, according to official returns). As Paz Estenssoro did not obtain an absolute majority, the selection of the next President should constitutionally have been made by the National Congress on 6 August from among the three highest candidates. However, on 16 May a military junta assumed responsibility for the Government with Brig. Gen. Hugo Ballivián Rojas as President.	
